            <br /><br />
            Innovation.
            <br />
            A word that is passed around a lot in the IT industry. What exactly is it? It is as
            straight forward as the definition provides? The action or process of innovating, a new method, idea, product, etc. There are new ideas every day, new conversations in so many aspects of
            life that it cannot be limited to what we discover with data. And it’s not and that is the beauty of it. Technology is not limited to the IT industry. There is a form of innovation at every
            corner. New ideas are being cast in retail, aviation and how I order my coffee. I have been asked Why Tech? Why did you decide on this industry? The reasons
            behind may get complicated but my answer is simple. I want to be a part of an industry of passion and whose intent is to better the lives of everybody. If I can save the soccer mom an extra
            five minutes in the morning – I would collaborate and create an application. If I can help brainstorm software that can be adopted into a medical facility or help the staff complete their
            jobs then I succeeded. Why tech wasn’t a question to make me think why I want to do this. This question made me think where I want to start and what company has the same values in taking
            care of the world. These ideas are ambitious for someone so new to the industry, but my fire for learning more has never been so driving for me and I am absolutely addicted to the enthusiasm.
            I believe it is possible to have an impact. I believe in such a fast-paced and developing industry everybody can add their own personal touch of innovation. I want to be surrounded by the people
            that ooze optimism as much as I do so I went into technology.
